The paper deals with self-calibration of visual-inertial sensor systems, which is a topic related to robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves optimization and selection of informative motion segments, which can be seen as a machine learning problem (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper also mentions energy constraints, which could be related to control systems (cs.SY).
